                  throws ServerOfflineException,
                         InvalidHumanKindException,

                         IncorrectFormatException,

        Checks the data passed is correct and if so, will create an alert in the system.
        Parameters:
        aEtHumanKind - the a et human kind
        year - is the year that the accident took place
        month - is the month that the accident took place
        day - is the day of the month that the accident took place
        hour - is the hour of the clock at the time that the accident took place
        minute - is the minute of the clock at the time that the accident took place
        second - is the second of the clock at the time that the accident took place
        phoneNumber - is the contact phone number of the person reporting the accident to the iCrashSystem.
        latitude - is the latitude point of where the accident happened
        longitude - is the longitude point of where the accident happened
        comment - is the
        Returns:
        Returns a PtBoolean of true if done successfully, otherwise will return a false
        Throws:
        ServerOfflineException - is an error that is thrown when the server is offline or not reachable
        InvalidHumanKindException - is thrown when the enum type of HumanKind does not match the specification
        ServerNotBoundException - is only thrown when attempting to access a server which has no current binding. This shouldn't happen, but you never know!
        IncorrectFormatException - is thrown when a Dt/Et information type does not match the is() method specified in the specification
        StringToNumberException - the string to number exception
